LightCTL dumb_Teensy is a part of the LightCTL software package.

It is designed to control a lamp using a Teensy microcontroller.

----------------------------------------------------------------

Features:


*Set Luminosity in Lux for the lamp
*Monitor luminoisty via python serial module, other serial module, or visually with 7-segment displays
*Closed loop control system maintains set luminosity indefinately
*Open Source


---------------------------------------------------------------

Getting started(Hardware):

	Get:
		All Prices in USD


		Item				Quantity	Price	Link
		Teensy2.0 			1		18 	http://pjrc.com/store/teensy.html
		7-Seg Displays			2		1.99	http://www.radioshack.com Model 276-075 | Catalog #: 276-075
		BCD to 7-Segment Decoder	1 		0.99	http://hobbyengineering.com/H1388.html
		Quad NAND gate			1		0.99	http://www.hobbyegineering.com/H1385.html
		CdS Phototresistors(5pk)	1		2.99	http://www.radioshack.com Model 176-1657 | Catalog #: 276-1657

There is a .pdf of the LightCTL circuit in the main directory. Build it!
		

---------------------------------------------------------------

Getting started(Software):

You'll need to set up the Teensy Loader Application, follow instructions here: http://pjrc.com/teensy/loader.html

You'll also need the Teensy C compiler: http://pjrc.com/teensy/gcc.html

If you don't want to set up a build environment you will find dumb_Teensy.hex and smart_Teensy.hex in the hex directoy
inside the main directory.

You'll need python: http://www.python.org/download/
and python serial: http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pyserial


---------------------------------------------------------------

Example Use:

	1) Build dumb_Teensy.c using the makefile.

	2) Use the Teensy Loader application to program the Teensy with dumb_Teensy.hex.

	3) Launch dumb_Teensy.py with your computer.

	4) Follow on-screen instructions!

